      <h2 id="quickbooks-hvac">QuickBooks Online: The Industry Standard for HVAC</h2>
      
      <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">
        <p>QuickBooks Online dominates HVAC accounting for good reason: it's built for businesses that need detailed job tracking, handles complex inventory management, and integrates natively with virtually every HVAC CRM and dispatch system on the market.</p>
        
        <p>The job costing features let you track labor, materials, and overhead costs for each installation, repair, or maintenance contract. You can see exactly which jobs made money and which lost money, down to the specific technician and material costs.</p>
        
        <p><strong>Key HVAC-Specific Features:</strong></p>
        <ul>
          <li>Job-level profitability tracking with real-time cost allocation</li>
          <li>Multi-location inventory management for trucks and warehouses</li>
          <li>Prevailing wage calculations and certified payroll reports</li>
          <li>Native integration with <a href="https://go.getjobber.com/bo42cjptz4m2" rel="sponsored nofollow">Jobber</a>, <a href="https://housecallpro.partnerlinks.io/auy5xcz257sw" rel="sponsored nofollow">HousecallPro</a>, and ServiceTitan</li>
          <li>Advanced reporting for contract vs. time-and-materials profitability</li>
        </ul>
        
        <p><strong>Pricing Structure (2026):</strong></p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Simple Start:</strong> $30/month (1 user, basic job tracking)</li>
          <li><strong>Essentials:</strong> $60/month (3 users, advanced job costing)</li>
          <li><strong>Plus:</strong> $90/month (5 users, inventory tracking, project profitability)</li>
          <li><strong>Advanced:</strong> $200/month (25 users, advanced reporting, custom fields)</li>
        </ul>
        
        <p>Most HVAC companies with 5-20 employees find the Plus plan ($90/month) provides the best value. The inventory tracking alone saves companies an average of $8,000-15,000 annually by reducing over-ordering and preventing stockouts.</p>
      </div>

      <div style="background: #e8f4f8; border: 1px solid #1B4F72; padding: 1.5rem; margin: 2rem 0; border-radius: 8px;">
        <h4 style="color: #1B4F72; margin-top: 0;">Real-World ROI Example</h4>
        <p style="margin-bottom: 0;">ABC Heating & Air (12 employees, $1.8M annual revenue) implemented QuickBooks Plus job costing and discovered their maintenance contracts were generating 31% margins while emergency repairs averaged only 8% margins. They restructured pricing and increased annual profits by $89,000 in year one. The $1,080 annual software cost delivered 82x ROI.</p>
      </div>

      <h2 id="freshbooks-hvac">FreshBooks: Service-First Approach for HVAC</h2>
      
      <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">
        <p>FreshBooks excels for HVAC contractors who do primarily service work, maintenance contracts, and smaller installations. The time tracking features are more intuitive than QuickBooks, making it easier for field technicians to log hours accurately.</p>
        
        <p>The project-based accounting works well for tracking installation jobs, but lacks the detailed inventory management that larger HVAC companies need for parts tracking across multiple trucks and locations.</p>
        
        <p><strong>HVAC-Friendly Features:</strong></p>
        <ul>
          <li>Simple project profitability tracking</li>
          <li>Mobile time tracking with GPS verification</li>
          <li>Automated invoice creation from project hours</li>
          <li>Basic expense categorization for materials and fuel</li>
          <li>Customer portal for maintenance contract communication</li>
        </ul>
        
        <p><strong>Limitations for HVAC:</strong></p>
        <ul>
          <li>No multi-location inventory tracking</li>
          <li>Limited CRM integrations (mostly through Zapier)</li>
          <li>Basic payroll features (no prevailing wage support)</li>
          <li>Simplified job costing compared to QuickBooks</li>
        </ul>
        
        <p><strong>Pricing (2026):</strong></p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Lite:</strong> $17/month (5 clients, basic invoicing)</li>
          <li><strong>Plus:</strong> $30/month (50 clients, time tracking, project management)</li>
          <li><strong>Premium:</strong> $55/month (500 clients, advanced reporting)</li>
          <li><strong>Select:</strong> $90/month (unlimited clients, custom fields)</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <h2 id="wave-hvac">Wave Accounting: Free Option with Limitations</h2>
      
      <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">
        <p>Wave offers genuine free accounting software that handles basic bookkeeping, invoicing, and expense tracking. For solo HVAC contractors or very small teams doing straightforward residential work, Wave can meet basic financial management needs.</p>
        
        <p>The limitations become apparent quickly for growing HVAC businesses. Job costing requires manual workarounds, inventory tracking is non-existent, and CRM integrations require expensive third-party tools or custom development.</p>
        
        <p><strong>What Wave Does Well:</strong></p>
        <ul>
          <li>Free basic accounting and invoicing</li>
          <li>Simple expense categorization</li>
          <li>Bank connection and transaction importing</li>
          <li>Basic financial reporting</li>
          <li>Receipt scanning mobile app</li>
        </ul>
        
        <p><strong>HVAC Limitations:</strong></p>
        <ul>
          <li>No native job costing or project profitability tracking</li>
          <li>No inventory management</li>
          <li>Limited payroll features ($20/month per employee)</li>
          <li>Manual CRM integration (if any)</li>
          <li>Basic reporting unsuitable for larger operations</li>
        </ul>
        
        <p><strong>Hidden Costs:</strong></p>
        <p>While Wave is "free," HVAC companies typically need additional tools to handle job costing ($50-150/month), inventory tracking ($30-80/month), and advanced reporting ($25-75/month). The total cost often exceeds QuickBooks Plus while providing inferior HVAC-specific functionality.</p>
      </div>

