      <h2 id="crm-integrations">CRM Integration Capabilities</h2>
      
      <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">
        <p>Your accounting software must connect seamlessly with your field service management system. Manual data entry between systems costs HVAC companies an average of 8-12 hours weekly and creates costly errors.</p>
        
        <p><strong>QuickBooks Online Integrations:</strong></p>
        <p>Native, two-way sync with <a href="https://go.getjobber.com/vcuhehgs796s" rel="sponsored nofollow">Jobber</a> transfers customer data, invoices, payments, and job costs automatically. Completed jobs in Jobber appear as properly categorized transactions in QuickBooks within minutes.</p>
        
        <p><a href="https://housecallpro.partnerlinks.io/auy5xcz257sw" rel="sponsored nofollow">HousecallPro's QuickBooks sync</a> handles invoice creation, payment recording, and customer management without manual intervention. Job materials and labor costs flow directly into job costing reports.</p>
        
        <p>For more details on CRM comparisons, see our analysis of <a href="/hvac/crm/jobber-vs-servicetitan">Jobber vs ServiceTitan</a> and <a href="/hvac/crm/housecall-pro-vs-jobber">HousecallPro vs Jobber</a>.</p>
        
        <p><strong>FreshBooks Integrations:</strong></p>
        <p>Limited native integrations require Zapier for most HVAC CRMs. Zapier costs $20-50/month additional and creates sync delays of 15-30 minutes. Data mapping requires technical setup that most contractors struggle with.</p>
        
        <p><strong>Wave Integrations:</strong></p>
        <p>No native HVAC CRM integrations. Custom API development costs $2,000-8,000 for basic sync functionality. Most Wave users manually export/import data weekly, creating accuracy issues and consuming 4-6 hours of administrative time.</p>
      </div>

